main event: A bright, star-like object of second magnitude, around twice the size of a pinhead, fell steadily downwards by three in Humboldt, Saskatchewan, Canada on October 27, 1957.
interesting points: The object was observed for 15 seconds.
The witness could not provide any further details that would aid in determining the nature of the sighting.
Although the sighting occurred in late 1957, it was not reported until late 1961.
A separate report mentions a woman observing a large, circular craft with flashing lights over the Humboldt highway about 7 miles southeast of Humboldt, Saskatchewan on October 24, 1955.
The witness of the circular craft had been trying to get up the courage to report the sighting for several days.
witnesses: Gerald W. Kinzel, a witness who wished to remain anonymous
